# CommandMenu SwiftUI disambiguation

All `Commands` structs in `Jot/App/` must use `SwiftUI.CommandMenu(...)` instead of bare `CommandMenu(...)`.

**Why:** The project has its own `CommandMenu` view in `Jot/Views/Components/CommandMenu.swift` (the command palette UI). Without the `SwiftUI.` prefix, the compiler resolves to the project's type, producing confusing errors about missing arguments for `tools:`, `isRevealed:`, etc.

**How to apply:** When creating new `Commands` structs (like `ViewMenuCommands`, `FormatMenuCommands`), always write `SwiftUI.CommandMenu("MenuName") { ... }`. All existing command files follow this pattern.
